B. Wayne Kingery (June 5, 1927 â€“ June 2, 2016) was an American football halfback and defensive back who played for the Baltimore Colts. He played college football at McNeese State University, having previously attended Lake Charles High School. He was inducted into the McNeese State Hall of Fame in 1980.
